If you're not using a BBQ, preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Soak the @bamboo skewers{6} in a dish of water. Bring a #medium saucepan{} to the boil with 1/2 tsp of @salt{}. Chop the @potatoes{450g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!), and add them to the boiling water. Simmer until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}, then drain in a #colander{} and pop into the #bowl{} you're going to serve them in to cool. Meanwhile, trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice, set aside. Zest the @lemon{1} and cut in half. In a #small bowl{}, add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and the lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together. Set aside - this is your dressing for the salad later.

Cut the @British chicken thighs{3} into 2cm pieces. Cut the @halloumi{250%g} into 2cm cubes. Skewer the chicken and halloumi on the skewers, alternating on each skewer. This should make three skewers per person. Season well and set aside for grilling later.

> Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Trim the bottom 2cm off of the @asparagus{100%g} and discard. Trim and thinly slice the @radishes{100%g}. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the asparagus and pan fry until slightly charred, ~{2-3%minutes}, turning regularly. Add a splash of water to the pan and keep cooking the asparagus until tender, ~{3-4%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper. Once cooked, pop the asparagus in a #large salad bowl{}, add the sliced radishes and set aside.

If you're cooking your @chorizo style pork sausages{4} in the oven, pop them on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with oil. Bake them on the top shelf of your oven until browned and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. You can also BBQ them instead if you want - just make sure they are cooked through!

Pop the #frying pan{} back on the heat (no need to wash), and drizzle with a splash of oil. Add the skewers. Pan fry the skewers turning every minute or so, until golden and charred, ~{8%minutes}. Drizzle them with the @honey{15%g} and cook for the last minute of cooking and turn to coat.

> You may need to cook these in batches depending on the size of your pan.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. You can also do this on the BBQ, make sure the chicken is cooked through.

Once everything is nearly ready, add the @mayonnaise{64%g}, @lemon{1}(zested), spring onion and @Dijon mustard{10%g} to the potato. Season with salt and pepper and mix until combined. Add the @pea shoots{40%g} to the asparagus and radish. Drizzle the lemon dressing onto salad and toss together. Serve the skewers with a couple of sausages per person and the 2 salads alongside. Enjoy!